snippet.textDisplay: My second favorite gen of camaro! The 70-73 split bumpers are my favorite but I own a 01 SS. They were the hot rods of my generation since I’m 22. I bought mine 3 years ago from a 65 year old man, car only had 58k miles and completely stock for 8k. Since then I’ve caged it, sold the ls1 put a fully forged iron 408 stroker, 12:1 compression. Full chromoly MWC suspension, th400 with brake, fab 9 inch, and have a direct port nitrous kit on the car. Made 530whp on motor and just on a 250 shot I made 870whp and my motor is capable of a 450 shot lol. There great cars and make the best drag cars but can be made into autocross monsters too

snippet.textDisplay: You do have 1 thing wrong... the SS is actually a functional Ram Air... it’s not a closed air box. The air is forced through the hood and into the lower section of the air box which passes through the filter, directly into the intake.

snippet.textDisplay: I can't understand why people have a problem with the style of the car. I mean, I get the meme but it was right right in line with sports car styling of the time. Think mkIV supra that we all can't get over, or late Acura nsx. That softened aerodynamic look was an artifact of the decade and you can see the elements in many cars. I think the car looks clean and uncluttered.  Also while the engineering wasn't the bleeding edge of technology the tech was proven and the numbers were unmatched at that price point.
